id: pm-urxb
title: Make lifecycle validate patterns configurable
description: Add settings-backed lifecycle validation pattern controls so closure-like and stale-blocker heuristics can be tuned per project without code changes.
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[4]: governance,lifecycle,pm-cli,validation
created_at: "2026-04-05T23:06:03.204Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-25T20:04:47.301Z"
deadline: "2026-05-09T17:10:36.291Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "pm validate lifecycle checks read configurable pattern lists from settings with deterministic fallback defaults, expose pattern-source metadata in details, and retain backward-compatible warning tokens unless policy explicitly changes behavior."
definition_of_ready: Current lifecycle validation baseline is merged and pattern tuning requirements are documented.
order: 3
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Reduce false positives and improve lifecycle validation portability
value: Projects can tune lifecycle heuristics without patching CLI code
impact: Improves validation signal quality across heterogeneous workflows
outcome: "Lifecycle validation becomes configurable, deterministic, and easier to adopt"
why_now: Today’s lifecycle hardening shipped static heuristics; configurable policy prevents future drift/false-positive churn.
